erited, he said, from an oldaunt. He was very drunk at the moment and seemed surprised when a week or solater on the eve of his departure I reminded him of his exuberantinvitation, which, it so happened, I alone had accepted. We both wereunpopular orphans, and should, I remarked, band together.

